	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100364683674949><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1479&mid=100364683674949>Helm changes colors!!</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1479&mid=100364683674949#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=112115><span id= >Ruok</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Oct 21st 2:47 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This has to be one of the coolest items I have ever seen.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am an erudite, and when I wear the helm it is the same color as whatever gloves I am wearing.  I always thought the helm was green, because when I got it I was wearing RFV gloves.  However, I just got the thurgadin quest gloves; when I put on the new gloves, the helm turned tan!  I decided to try a few more gloves, and sure enough the helm changed colors every time I changed gloves.  This is quite convenient!  No matter what, the FFH will always match the color of your gloves.<br><br>BTW I waited for the druid in LFay to spawn for 5-6 hours a day for over a week with no luck.  She finally spawned when the server came back up after a patch.  I logged in and there she was, right where these boards say she is.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
